"{\n  \"text\": \"When I'm at the farmer's market, people ask me what's the healthiest fermented food I can eat. I always tell them kimchi. And that's not because kimchi is any more healthy than uh or the cabbage and kimchi is better than the cabbage and sauerkraut, or it's better than fermented beets or fermented turnips. It's because there's seven different vegetables in my kimchi. And what you're looking for when you're eating fermented foods is biodiversity. Biodiversity means that you're getting a lot of different types of cultures in your food, and that's what you're trying to do. You're trying to influence your gut. And the trick is that your gut is constantly changing. Bacteria is very fluid. And so by giving it a lot of different information, a lot of different genes and tools that it uses, you can give it uh you can access it from all sides. And this is one of the things that it favors over a probiotic. And a probiotic is a single proprietary bacteria strain done many, many times at someone's patent, and this lacks biodiversity, and that's why fermented foods are often so much more effective than probiotics. Hey, anyway, thanks y'all. See ya.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" When I'm at the farmer's market, people ask me what's the healthiest fermented food I can eat.\",\n      \"start\": 0.24,\n      \"end\": 4.4,\n      \"duration\": 4.16,\n      \"confidence\": 0.993,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" W\",\n          \"start\": 0.24,\n          \"end\": 0.32,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.997\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"hen\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.48,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" I\",\n          \"start\": 0.48,\n          \"end\": 0.56,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.998\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"'\",\n         